# Cursor Internal Services

## Available Services (via createDecorator)

| Service | DI String | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| `composerDataService` | `"composerDataService"` | Manages composer data, handles, and state |
| `composerChatService` | `"composerChatService"` | Submits messages, manages chat flow |
| `composerEventService` | `"composerEventService"` | Fires events (e.g. force text update) |
| `composerViewsService` | `"composerViewsService"` | Controls UI views, focus, scroll |
| `composerModesService` | `"composerModesService"` | Agent/Plan/Ask/Debug mode switching |
| `modelConfigService` | `"modelConfigService"` | Model selection and configuration |

## Key Methods

### composerDataService (DS)
- `getHandleIfLoaded(composerId)` ‚Äî returns handle or null
- `updateComposerData(handle, {text, richText})` ‚Äî updates input text
- `selectedComposerId` ‚Äî currently focused composer
- `allComposersData.allComposers` ‚Äî all composers with metadata
- `allComposersData.selectedComposerIds` ‚Äî open composer IDs
- `getComposerData(handle)` ‚Äî full composer data including modelConfig

### composerChatService (CS)
- `submitChatMaybeAbortCurrent(composerId, text, opts)` ‚Äî main submission
  - `opts.modelOverride` ‚Äî override model for this request
  - `opts.forceBubbleId` ‚Äî force specific bubble
  - `opts.skipClearInput` ‚Äî don't clear input after submit
  - `opts.isPlanExecution` ‚Äî executing a plan

### composerEventService (ES)
- `fireShouldForceText({composerId})` ‚Äî forces UI to update with new text

### composerViewsService (VS)
- `showAndFocus(composerId)` ‚Äî activates and focuses a composer tab

### composerModesService (MS)
- `setComposerUnifiedMode(handle, modeId)` ‚Äî set mode (must be called BEFORE submit)
- `getComposerUnifiedMode(composerId)` ‚Äî get current mode
- `getAllModes()` ‚Äî returns `[{id, name, icon, description, ...}]`
- Available modes: `agent`, `plan`, `chat` (Ask), `debug`, `triage`, `spec`, `project`, `background`

### modelConfigService (MC)
- `setModelConfigForComposer(handle, {modelName})` ‚Äî set model on specific composer
- `setModelConfig("composer", {modelName, maxMode})` ‚Äî set global composer model
- `getModelConfig("composer")` ‚Äî get current config
- `getAvailableDefaultModels()` ‚Äî list of `{name, displayName, defaultOn, ...}`
- `getSelectedModelsForComposer(handle)` ‚Äî models selected on a composer

## Wait-for-Handle Pattern

Composer handles may not be loaded immediately after `showAndFocus`. Always poll:

```javascript
await vs.showAndFocus(composerId);
var h = ds.getHandleIfLoaded(composerId);
if (!h) {
  for (var w = 0; w < 40; w++) {
    await new Promise(function(r) { setTimeout(r, 50) });
    h = ds.getHandleIfLoaded(composerId);
    if (h) break;
  }
}
```

## Mode Must Be Set Before Submit

`submitChatMaybeAbortCurrent` reads the mode via `getComposerUnifiedMode(composerId)` internally. The mode must be set on the handle **before** calling submit:

```javascript
if (e.mode) ms.setComposerUnifiedMode(h, e.mode);
if (e.modelOverride) mc.setModelConfigForComposer(h, {modelName: e.modelOverride});
// Then submit
await cs.submitChatMaybeAbortCurrent(t, text, {modelOverride: e.modelOverride});
```

## Injection Code Style

Injected code must be compatible with comma-expression context (inserted after a `registerCommand()` call). Rules:
- No arrow functions at the top level of the comma expression on older builds; use `async(n,e)=>{}` inside `registerCommand` calls
- Use `var` not `let`/`const` (minifier compatibility)
- Use `function` keyword for nested callbacks if arrow functions cause parsing issues
- All code must be a single expression (no standalone statements)
